The paper deals with the minrank of graphs, which is closely related to index coding, network coding, and distributed storage, all of which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves analyzing the properties of random graphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of minrank also has connections to circuit complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves analyzing the structure of graphs, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG).
